### Enrichment
The 2026 International AI Safety Report specifically advocates defense-in-depth with multiple safeguards. New privacy laws in 2026: California Training Data Transparency Act (AB2013), EU AI Act enforcement, 8 new US state privacy laws. The three-layer approach (deterministic scanning, LLM filtering, human gate) aligns with regulatory best practices. The 'failures are safe' design principle (default private) is particularly relevant given that all major AI providers now train on user inputs by default (since Sep 2025).

